research_municipality_step.notes: Jasper, Texas operates under a Council-Manager form of government, which is a variation of the mayor-council system. The city council consists of a mayor and five council members. The Mayor and Council Members for Districts 1 and 2 were sworn into office on May 6, 2025. The terms for the Mayor and Council Members for Districts 1 and 2 end in May 2027, while the terms for Council Members for Districts 3, 4, and 5 At-Large end in May 2026.
